Eu só tenho que agradecer por esse ano. 
Por 2022 razões que fizeram eu não desistir. Eu não desistir de viver, de lutar pelos meus sonhos, mesmo ainda não alcançados. 
2022 pessoas que passaram pela minha vida essa ano, e me ensinaram que eu não sou perfeito, santo, ou desgraça. Eu sou apenas mais um, igual a todos. 
2022 momentos em que eu, por só pensar em mim, não enxerguei o lado do outro, e o critiquei ao invés de perguntar “como está seu dia?” 
2022 vezes em que eu me escondi por detrás de alguém por ter vergonha de mim mesmo. 
2022 vezes em que eu poderia ajudar mais. Ter dito eu te amo. Ter ligado ao invés de esperar uma ligação. 
2022 vezes em que pessoas lá mostraram que eu tenho que parar de criar expectativas em outros. 
Enfim. Que em 2023 eu seja um ser humano melhor em todos os sentidos.
Obrigado 2022.

A number of factors can contribute to back pain at work. For example:

Force. Exerting too much force on your back — such as by lifting or moving heavy objects — can cause injury.
Repetition. Repeating certain movements, especially those that involve twisting or rotating your spine, can injure your back.
Inactivity. An inactive job or a desk job can contribute to back pain, especially if you have poor posture or sit all day in a chair with inadequate back support.

social_posts.post_text:
I remember when I was 19 years old, walking on the streets of my hometown in Brazil, delivering my resume and looking for jobs, I went to a travel agency office and I asked “what do I have to do to go to USA?”. 
The person asked me what documents I had, and I said that I only had my ID. She kind of laughed on me. 
Life was hard because I didn’t want to live anymore with that animal that one day I called father. No matter where, I just wanted to scape. 
24 years later, I moved to The United States of America, with no English, no profession, just dreams. The beginning was hard, specially when the money that I saved to move here started to end, and I couldn’t work because the legal papers was in process. 
I remember one day Greg and I went to the groceries store and we had to back some stuff because we didn’t have all the money. I cried inside myself and behind him, but I promised that it would never happen again. 
In 2017 I started barber school, and the rest of the history until now YOU ALREADY KNOW. 
I heard some people from Brazil telling me that I would go back because I couldn’t handle the new language, new life, new everything. I love when someone tells me that I can’t do something. I F…KING love it! Always doubt on me. You have no idea how hungry I get. 
Anyway. If you have a dream, and you pray so many times for help, but your dream never comes true, be patience. Even if you already gave up or forgot about it. God is working on it. And you will receive your blessings on the right time. 
“God does not move a straw as far as your ability can, but God moves the heaven where you cannot.”
What happened today I believe that’s the most amazing dream that I could reach. I feel better, I feel proud of myself, I feel that I did reach my biggest goal. 
I don’t have to mention names, but I do appreciate all of you who helped me trough all this ups and downs. I will never forget who was there for me when no one else was. 
My Americans fellows will never understand how amazing is to live here in USA. Unless you’re like me, born in a 3rd world. 

Do you remember that guy from Brazil with no English, no professional, just dreams?

Today he became an American citizen. 🇺🇸

For who don’t know, Phoenix is a rescued Pit. We found her online at @humanebroward. 
Phoenix was dumped on the shelter by one of those irresponsible breeders that use dogs to breed and make money on them. She was 33lbs when she arrived at the shelter, and now 6 months later, she is not only 77lbs, but a happy dog with a heart that no words can describe the happiness that she gives to everybody around her. Like I always say, a rescued dog has a different kind of love. A grateful kind of love.  We can see it in her eyes how much trauma she had in the past and now, living her best life, she is just love ♥️. 
The only way we can stop this brutality that affects the life of so many dogs, is to not buy any dogs from these persons who abuse animals for breeding purposes. Don’t feed the pocket of these people that treat dogs in the worse way possible. 
When you are ready to include a dog in your life and family, please go check the shelters around your area. They are full of then waiting to have a decent life, and give to you the most unconditional love.
Now I am becoming even more involved in this cause of rescuing dogs, and blessed to be invited by the talented photographer @mikeruizone to be part of the 2024 calendar called Hunks and Hounds, which this year the calendar will benefits an amazing rescue called @louieslegacy animal rescue, which helps dogs that have been abandoned, neglected, and abused by taking them from shelters where they are languishing and finding them loving, fur-ever homes. And 100% of the proceeds go to that organization! 
As soon the calendar is ready, I will post the link on my social medias for purchase. 
Thank you all that support me, and specially the furry babies that needs our help!
